Illicit liquor brewers in Kiambu county have been warned to either stop the illegal business or they rot in jail. County commissioner Wilson Wanyanga said the government will not relent in the fight against illicit liquor. He said anyone caught brewing, selling or consuming the illicit brew will be prosecuted.This is after Police in Thika west and Gatundu North sub-counties raided famously known notorious brewing dens along the Chania River, Makwa area and destroyed more than 2,000 litres of Kangara, a type of illicit brew commonly consumed in the area. He said that the brewing barons behind the massive brewing in Kiambu County are being investigating and will be dealt with according to the law if caught.